Important offers, pricing details, & disclaimers


60% off software offer is valid for new and upgrade QuickBooks Point of Sale Desktop 12.0 customers who sign up and are approved for a new QuickBooks Payment account by calling Intuit at (866) 272-8737 or who currently have a QuickBooks Payments. Offer expires 7/28/2017 and is subject to change without notice.

QuickBooks Point of Sale Desktop 12.0 software is EMV ready. Full EMV Compliance requires QuickBooks Point of Sale Desktop 12.0 Software, a QuickBooks Payments account, and an EMV ready Ingenico iPP 350 PIN Pad (sold separately). QuickBooks Payments accounts are subject to credit and application approval. See the Merchant Agreement for complete terms and conditions, including additional pricing information. To apply, you must be eligible under our Acceptable Use Policy.Terms, conditions, prices, payment, features and services are subject to change.
QuickBooks POS Desktop 12.0 integrates with QuickBooks Pro/Premier (2013-2015) and QuickBooks Enterprise (13.0, 14.0, 2015). Sold separately. Auto payment reconciliation works with Quickbooks Pro, Pro Plus, Premier, Premier Plus, or Enterprise 2015. User must have QuickBooks Point of Sale software, Quickbooks Desktop 2015(see versions above), and a POS Merchant Service account in order to use auto payment reconciliation.
10x faster startup time based on testing against QuickBooks Point of Sale 2013 R1 release. Faster workflows based on testing against QuickBooks POS 2013 R12 release for: loading customer lists, loading inventory item lists, looking up specific inventory items, and looking up specific customers.

Terms, conditions, pricing, features, service, and support options are subject to change without notice.



















